<br>
Almost all pet related questions belong in PETS.  Only if it were viewed entirely as a spell and not as a pet would SPELLS be appropriate.  For example, if you wanted to know how much the 54 Water Pet sells for on various servers, or where it drops, then you are interested in it as a SPELL.  On the other hand, if you want to know how much the 54 Water Pet backstabs for, or whether it benefits from the damage focus bracer, you are interested in it as a PET.<br>
<br>
I have no problems with anything you have posted so far.  While they are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;newbie&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> questions, they have been well received and generated a lot of thoughtful responses.<br>
<br>
The problem I have is when people ask the same damn question that has been asked a million times and which already has numerous threads in the appropriate forum.  These questions just clutter up GENERAL.<br>
